-- BofA nears $16-$17 bln settlement with DoJ - WSJ
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 04:16PM EDT
-- None



Aug 6 (Reuters) - Bank of America Corp <BAC.N> is close to a deal with the U.S. Justice Department to pay between $16 billion and $17 billion to resolve allegations of mortgage-related misconduct in the run-up to the financial crisis, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter.

